    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-02T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-02T05:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                        >Baker, Charles</persName>/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-02T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 2, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. 1. <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> has now received further word from <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName>’s captors who have reduced
                    their demands to $200,000 and 2,000 boxes of ammunition.</p>
                <p>2. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_HC1">Ho Chen-chun</persName> now informs me
                    that his messengers are useless in dealing with the group of bandits who hold
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName>. The only thing <pb
                        facs="0568" n="470" xml:id="pg_470"/> General Ho will promise after repeated
                    interviews is a military expedition against <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName>’s captors. I doubt his power
                    to accomplish this and in any event it would not help <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName>.</p>
                <p>3. I have therefore, after consultation with Admiral <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_WRAYS1">Williams</persName>, wired <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_HL1">Hoyt</persName> suggesting that he instruct his
                    agent at Ichang to proceed at once to <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> near Pailochi
                    and conduct negotiations with the bandits in accordance with his original
                    plan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
